---
/**
 * Platform Overview — Internal stakeholder page
 *
 * Shows non-technical audience the full scope of what's been built,
 * what's ready now, and what becomes available over time.
 * Not linked from navigation — shared directly via URL.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Platform Overview" description="SCA digital platform — what's built and what's possible" containerClass="overview-layout" noindex>
  <div class="ov">
    <div class="ov-header">
      <h1 class="ov-header__title">SCA Digital Platform</h1>
      <p class="ov-header__subtitle">
        What's been built, what's ready now, and what it means for the team.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Problem -->
    <section class="ov-section">
      <h2 class="ov-section__title">Why This Exists</h2>
      <p>The previous website had no structured way to manage content. Updating a page, posting news, or changing an image required a developer. There was no content model — no organized system describing what kinds of content the school has and how they relate to each other.</p>
      <p>This platform gives SCA a real content management system. Editors can update text, swap images, add news, and manage pages without writing code or waiting on a developer.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Feature Grid -->
    <section class="ov-section">
      <h2 class="ov-section__title">What's Here</h2>
      <p class="ov-section__intro">Each row below is a capability of the platform. Some are ready for launch; others are built and waiting for the right time.</p>

      <div class="ov-grid">
        <!-- Ready Now -->
        <div class="ov-card ov-card--ready">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Ready for launch</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Editable Pages</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">About, Admissions, Academics, Athletics, Student Life, Community, Engagement, Contact — all manageable through the CMS. Text, images, and page sections can be changed by editors.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--ready">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Ready for launch</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">News &amp; Updates</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">News articles with images, summaries, and dates. Can be created and published directly from the CMS. Chelsea's SCA news project can connect to this system.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--ready">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Ready for launch</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Navigation &amp; Footer</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Menu links, footer sections, and social media links are all CMS-managed. No code changes needed to reorganize the site navigation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--ready">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Ready for launch</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Site Settings</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">School name, address, phone, email, social links, enrollment URL, and announcement banner — all editable in one place.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--ready">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Ready for launch</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Page Builder</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Pages are built from reusable sections — hero banners, text blocks, image galleries, call-to-action bars, testimonials, and more. Editors can rearrange sections without developer help.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--ready">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Ready for launch</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Accessibility</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Text contrast, image descriptions, keyboard navigation, and screen reader support have been audited and corrected across all pages.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Available When Ready -->
        <div class="ov-card ov-card--available">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Built — launch when ready</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Student Projects Showcase</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">A proof of concept for future submissions, tested with dummy Workspace accounts and sample content.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--available">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Built — launch when ready</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Faculty &amp; Staff Directory</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Person profiles with photos, titles, departments, and bios. Ready to populate with real staff information when the team is prepared.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--available">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Built — launch when ready</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Events Calendar</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Event listings with dates, descriptions, and locations. Schema is in place; content can be added when the school is ready to publish events publicly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--available">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Built — launch when ready</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Alumni Stories</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">A place to feature alumni experiences and outcomes. Structured for quotes, photos, and graduation details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--available">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Built — launch when ready</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Visual Editing</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Editors can preview changes on the actual website before publishing. Click on any text or image in the preview to jump directly to it in the CMS.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Future -->
        <div class="ov-card ov-card--future">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Possible next steps</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Automated News from Social Media</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">The system is designed to accept news from external sources (Instagram, external feeds). With some configuration, Chelsea's social media posts could automatically appear as news items on the site.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--future">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Possible next steps</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Media Galleries</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">Photo and video galleries for events, campus life, and programs. The content type exists in the CMS; front-end display can be added when there's demand.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ov-card ov-card--future">
          <div class="ov-card__status">Possible next steps</div>
          <h3 class="ov-card__title">Multi-Language Support</h3>
          <p class="ov-card__desc">The CMS structure supports adding translated content fields. Useful for SCA's international family audience. Requires content translation work, not code changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <section class="ov-section">
      <h2 class="ov-section__title">How Editing Works</h2>
      <div class="ov-steps">
        <div class="ov-step">
          <div class="ov-step__number">1</div>
          <div class="ov-step__content">
            <h3 class="ov-step__title">Log into the CMS</h3>
            <p>Go to the Studio (a web app) and sign in. No software to install.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ov-step">
          <div class="ov-step__number">2</div>
          <div class="ov-step__content">
            <h3 class="ov-step__title">Find what you want to change</h3>
            <p>Content is organized by type — pages, news, programs, settings. Click into any item to edit it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ov-step">
          <div class="ov-step__number">3</div>
          <div class="ov-step__content">
            <h3 class="ov-step__title">Make your changes</h3>
            <p>Edit text, upload images, rearrange sections. Changes are saved as drafts — nothing goes live until you publish.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ov-step">
          <div class="ov-step__number">4</div>
          <div class="ov-step__content">
            <h3 class="ov-step__title">Publish</h3>
            <p>When you're satisfied, hit Publish. The website updates within seconds.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What's Needed -->
    <section class="ov-section">
      <h2 class="ov-section__title">What's Needed From the Team</h2>
      <ul class="ov-list">
        <li>Review the site content for accuracy — facts, dates, names, descriptions</li>
        <li>Flag images that should be replaced with better or more current photos</li>
        <li>Identify any pages or sections that are missing or don't make sense</li>
        <li>Decide which sections (Student Projects, Faculty, Events) to include at launch</li>
        <li>Coordinate DNS cutover with the authorized account owner.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @import '../../styles/global.css';

  :global(.main-content:has(.overview-layout)) {
    padding: 0;
  }

  .ov {
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--container-padding) var(--space-20);
  }

  .ov-header {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--gold-500);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .ov-header__title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-4xl);
    color: var(--navy-900);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }

  .ov-header__subtitle {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--neutral-new-600);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
  }

  .ov-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .ov-section__title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    color: var(--navy-800);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
  }

  .ov-section__intro {
    color: var(--neutral-new-600);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .ov-section p {
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
    color: var(--neutral-new-900);
  }

  /* Feature Grid */
  .ov-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  @media (min-width: 40rem) {
    .ov-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .ov-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--neutral-new-200);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-6);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--neutral-new-200);
  }

  .ov-card--ready {
    border-top-color: var(--gold-500);
  }

  .ov-card--available {
    border-top-color: var(--navy-600);
  }

  .ov-card--future {
    border-top-color: var(--neutral-new-300);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .ov-card__status {
    font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .ov-card--ready .ov-card__status {
    color: var(--gold-600);
  }

  .ov-card--available .ov-card__status {
    color: var(--navy-600);
  }

  .ov-card--future .ov-card__status {
    color: var(--neutral-new-600);
  }

  .ov-card__title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    color: var(--navy-800);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  .ov-card__desc {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--neutral-new-600);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Steps */
  .ov-steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .ov-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .ov-step__number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--navy-800);
    color: #ffffff;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  }

  .ov-step__title {
    font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    color: var(--navy-800);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
  }

  .ov-step__content p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--neutral-new-600);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* List */
  .ov-list {
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
  }

  .ov-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    color: var(--neutral-new-900);
  }
</style>
